history.text: I absolutely love this movie! It is so funny and Lindsay Lohan is the perfect Cady Heron!
Yes and it is very true to Queen Bees!
It deserved more than %84 on Rotten Tomatos
I never read the book Queen Bees and Wannabes. I also enjoy Tina Fey as the screenwriter she does an awesome job
Yes I agree but rotten tomatoes is usually pretty strict in their reviews and do no favor comedies as much as other genres.

I agree with Rotten Tomatoes that this movie is a "
Top 50 Greatest Teen Comedies"
Mark Waters did a great job directing.
Yes he did a phenomenal job directing and the characters were casted perfectly.

Peter Travers review was spot on I think this is "comic gold"
yes the key scenes in this movie were very entertaining! I liked Janis and Damien a lot!
They were trying to help Cady adjust to school in America
I enjoyed Regina's character because she was really relatable to some girls in high school today
It is understandable that someone who was homeschooled would feel bewildered when entering high school
I usually look at Rotten Tomatoes critic score before watching a movie
Yes and someone who lived in Africa for the past 12 years
Evanston, Illinois is very different from Africa
Yes it is!
Do you like movies from the comedy genre?
The movie seems to have scored better on Cinema Score than the other two websites mentioned
Yes that is a keen observation. Like I mentioned earlier, I think it is harder for comedies to score as well.
The scene where the Burn book is released to the school and the massive brawl ensues is hilarious!
Yes it is.
It was suprising to see the Regina character break her spine in what I thought was going to be a light hearted comedy
What did you think of the scene where Regina George gets hit by the bus and breaks her spine?
Yes i thought it was a dream or imaginative but it was not and I was surprised by that
I can't believe the math teacher was dealing drugs
It took a great deal of courage for Cady to take blame for the burn book and become an outcast. What do you think of her actions?
It's good she didn't just drop out of school
Yes that is true. She faced her problems instead of running away of them.
Her performance at the math competition was impressive
Yes very impressive and she wins the mathletes competition for her team!
Yes this can't be easy. Illinois is a big state and there must be a lot of high schools in the competition
What do you think of Cady and Shane Oman winning Queen and King at the Spring Fling dance?
Another surprising turn of events
What do you think about it?
Yes it was very surprising but I think it was deserved.
And she made a nice gesture by breaking her tiara
and distributing the pieces to the other girls
Yes that was a great scene! In the end she reconciles with Janis, Damian, and Arron, and reaches a truce with the Plastics
